00:13:07.773 --> 00:13:11.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please give your attention
to Brother Harold Corkern,

00:13:11.360 --> 00:13:13.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
a helper to the Publishing Committee,

00:13:13.904 --> 00:13:16.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
as he develops the theme

00:13:16.240 --> 00:13:21.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Put Away’ Peace Wreckers
—Inappropriate Boasting.”

00:13:29.086 --> 00:13:33.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
What comes to your mind
when you hear the expression “put away”?

00:13:33.924 --> 00:13:36.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
You may think of related expressions

00:13:36.009 --> 00:13:40.681 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as “cast aside,” “dispose of,”

00:13:40.681 --> 00:13:43.392 line:90% position:50% align:center
“discard,” “get rid of.”

00:13:45.185 --> 00:13:48.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did we have to put away
to become a Christian?

00:13:48.480 --> 00:13:50.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible in the book

00:13:50.482 --> 00:13:55.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Ephesians 4:22
provides the answer.

00:13:55.279 --> 00:13:57.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s Ephesians 4:22:

00:13:59.074 --> 00:14:03.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You were taught
to put away the old personality

00:14:03.829 --> 00:14:06.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that conforms
to your former course of conduct

00:14:06.916 --> 00:14:11.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that is being corrupted
according to its deceptive desires.”

00:14:11.670 --> 00:14:15.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we had “to put away the old personality.”

00:14:15.966 --> 00:14:18.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it’s one thing to put it away;

00:14:18.302 --> 00:14:21.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s something else to keep it away.

00:14:21.263 --> 00:14:24.433 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s why
in the very next verse, verse 23,

00:14:24.433 --> 00:14:27.019 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul encourages us to do this:

00:14:27.019 --> 00:14:30.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And you should continue to be made new

00:14:30.564 --> 00:14:33.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
in your dominant mental attitude.”

00:14:33.526 --> 00:14:36.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s so important to keep it away,

00:14:36.070 --> 00:14:38.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
because the old personality has traits

00:14:38.864 --> 00:14:41.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
that can become peace wreckers.

00:14:43.411 --> 00:14:47.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
This symposium
will consider five peace wreckers

00:14:47.165 --> 00:14:51.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we should put away and keep away.

00:14:51.002 --> 00:14:54.005 line:90% position:50% align:center
Each talk will include
the following main points:

00:14:54.005 --> 00:14:58.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
(1) It will define the peace wrecker,

00:14:58.760 --> 00:15:02.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
(2) it will explain how it wrecks peace,

00:15:02.513 --> 00:15:06.517 line:90% position:50% align:center
and (3) we will consider how to put it away.

00:15:07.977 --> 00:15:11.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
What is the very first one
that we’re going to talk about?

00:15:11.898 --> 00:15:16.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
It is inappropriate boasting.

00:15:16.235 --> 00:15:18.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
What is inappropriate boasting?

00:15:18.863 --> 00:15:21.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
Basically, it’s self-praise,

00:15:21.616 --> 00:15:24.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the Bible condemns self-praise

00:15:24.410 --> 00:15:27.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice Proverbs 27:2:

00:15:27.956 --> 00:15:30.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Let someone else praise you,

00:15:30.333 --> 00:15:32.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and not your own mouth;

00:15:32.502 --> 00:15:35.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
others, and not your own lips.”

00:15:37.298 --> 00:15:40.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
Self-praise is an evidence of pride

00:15:40.802 --> 00:15:45.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
that causes one
to elevate himself above others.

00:15:45.348 --> 00:15:48.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some might develop an unhealthy pride

00:15:48.184 --> 00:15:52.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
about their accomplishments,
even in the ministry.

00:15:52.439 --> 00:15:54.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
It happened in the first century.

00:15:54.774 --> 00:15:57.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul had to write
to the Corinthian congregation

00:15:57.611 --> 00:15:59.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the dissensions that they were having,

00:15:59.779 --> 00:16:01.865 line:90% position:50% align:center
the lack of peace they were experiencing.

00:16:01.865 --> 00:16:03.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:16:03.199 --> 00:16:07.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, some in the congregation
were “puffed up with pride” about themselves

00:16:07.329 --> 00:16:09.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
or other men,

00:16:09.331 --> 00:16:12.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as Paul, Apollos, Cephas.

00:16:14.002 --> 00:16:16.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were giving
too much attention to themselves

00:16:16.797 --> 00:16:18.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to other men.

00:16:19.800 --> 00:16:22.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, how could that happen today?

00:16:22.552 --> 00:16:24.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, let’s imagine
a group of brothers talking,

00:16:24.763 --> 00:16:27.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
and one in the group says,

00:16:27.057 --> 00:16:30.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With Jehovah’s help
and with diligent prayer and effort,

00:16:30.560 --> 00:16:33.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
I finally got a Bible study.”

00:16:33.814 --> 00:16:37.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
But right away,
another one in the group proudly declares,

00:16:37.859 --> 00:16:40.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I have four Bible studies;

00:16:40.112 --> 00:16:45.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
two are attending meetings,
and one will soon be baptized.”

00:16:45.117 --> 00:16:47.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
Could such a statement be a peace wrecker?

00:16:49.454 --> 00:16:54.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
How does inappropriate boasting
wreck peace?

00:16:54.459 --> 00:16:57.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s not wrong
to take pleasure in our work

00:16:57.588 --> 00:17:01.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to thank Jehovah
for the success that we may have.

00:17:01.592 --> 00:17:04.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
But inappropriate boasting
about our accomplishments

00:17:04.720 --> 00:17:08.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
can stir up competition, envy, and rivalry.

00:17:09.975 --> 00:17:12.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
We must remember that self-promotion

00:17:12.603 --> 00:17:15.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
does not originate
with our heavenly Father, “the God of peace.”

00:17:15.773 --> 00:17:18.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
Where does it originate?

00:17:18.067 --> 00:17:20.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
First John 2:16 says:

00:17:20.361 --> 00:17:23.197 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The showy display of one’s means of life

00:17:23.197 --> 00:17:25.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
“does not originate with the Father,

00:17:25.491 --> 00:17:28.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
but originates with the world.”

00:17:28.494 --> 00:17:33.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
And would you not agree
that the world is filled with self-praise?

00:17:33.499 --> 00:17:36.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even on their social media, we see this.

00:17:36.752 --> 00:17:39.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of the material
that people post on social media

00:17:39.797 --> 00:17:43.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
is designed to make one
appear very important.

00:17:43.801 --> 00:17:45.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it is a showy display

00:17:45.803 --> 00:17:48.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
of their accomplishments,
their material possessions,

00:17:48.639 --> 00:17:52.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
or their expensive vacations that they enjoy.

00:17:52.977 --> 00:17:57.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
In other words, it’s all about “look at me.”

00:17:57.606 --> 00:18:00.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we want to avoid getting caught up

00:18:00.151 --> 00:18:02.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the world’s spirit of self-promotion

00:18:02.945 --> 00:18:05.072 line:90% position:50% align:center
that wrecks peace.

00:18:06.574 --> 00:18:09.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
To illustrate just how devastating

00:18:09.035 --> 00:18:12.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
the peace wrecker’s
inappropriate boasting can be,

00:18:12.830 --> 00:18:16.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s briefly consider
the Bible character Haman.

00:18:16.834 --> 00:18:19.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
He was a proud and haughty man,

00:18:19.295 --> 00:18:21.339 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he boasted a lot.

00:18:21.339 --> 00:18:23.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
Esther chapter 5 tells us

00:18:23.382 --> 00:18:25.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he was boasting
with his family and friends

00:18:25.718 --> 00:18:28.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
about his wealth, his many sons,

00:18:28.554 --> 00:18:31.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
how the king had promoted him
to a high station,

00:18:31.432 --> 00:18:33.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he was above all the other servants,

00:18:33.643 --> 00:18:36.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that he’d had a special meal, or banquet,

00:18:36.479 --> 00:18:38.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the king and queen.

00:18:39.857 --> 00:18:42.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Haman was hateful and arrogant.

00:18:42.694 --> 00:18:46.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he was plotting to kill
Jehovah’s faithful servant Mordecai.

00:18:47.865 --> 00:18:51.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
But his scheme
and his attitudes were exposed.

00:18:51.077 --> 00:18:52.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what happened?

00:18:52.954 --> 00:18:55.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
The very stake that Haman had built

00:18:55.039 --> 00:18:59.169 line:90% position:50% align:center
to hang Mordecai on he was hung on.

00:18:59.169 --> 00:19:01.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it reminds us
—doesn’t it?—

00:19:01.379 --> 00:19:05.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
that at Isaiah 29:20, the Bible says:

00:19:05.383 --> 00:19:09.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The boaster will come to his finish.”

00:19:09.721 --> 00:19:11.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
So because of the devastating effects

00:19:11.806 --> 00:19:15.143 line:90% position:50% align:center
that improper boasting
can have on ourselves and others,

00:19:15.143 --> 00:19:19.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
we do not even want
to give the impression of boasting.

00:19:20.607 --> 00:19:22.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the following dramatization,

00:19:22.942 --> 00:19:25.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
notice how a sister’s actions

00:19:25.278 --> 00:19:28.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
are misunderstood as boasting.

00:19:31.910 --> 00:19:34.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Put away from yourselves every kind

00:19:34.287 --> 00:19:38.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
“of malicious bitterness, anger, wrath,

00:19:38.667 --> 00:19:41.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
“screaming, and abusive speech,

00:19:41.586 --> 00:19:44.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as everything injurious.”

00:19:44.965 --> 00:19:47.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did anyone start the day thinking,

00:19:47.300 --> 00:19:52.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I believe I’ll show malicious bitterness
to my brother today’?

00:19:52.180 --> 00:19:54.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course not! 

00:19:54.266 --> 00:19:56.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet the potential is there, isn’t it?

00:19:57.769 --> 00:20:01.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
But genuine affection fights peace wreckers.

00:20:01.898 --> 00:20:06.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
And affection grows when we really know
our brothers and sisters well.

00:20:06.903 --> 00:20:11.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
We remember their joys

00:20:11.033 --> 00:20:13.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
and pains,

00:20:14.578 --> 00:20:17.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
their selfless zeal,

00:20:17.414 --> 00:20:20.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
how they came to love Jehovah,

00:20:22.044 --> 00:20:24.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
and what they endure.

